                    <h2 class="ctpl-c-types-heading">Types of Leave</h2>
                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="row ctpl-c-types-divs d-flex">
                                    <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12 ctpl-c-types-divs-div">
                                        <h3 class="ctpl-c-types-divs-div-subheading">Continuous Leave</h3>
                                        <p class="ctpl-c-types-divs-div-para"> An absence taken as a consecutive span of time for a single qualifying reason.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12 ctpl-c-types-divs-div">
                                        <h3 class="ctpl-c-types-divs-div-subheading">Intermittent Leave</h3>
                                        <p class="ctpl-c-types-divs-div-para"> A leave in separate, non-consecutive time periods rather than a single span of time for a single qualifying reason.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12 ctpl-c-types-divs-div">
                                        <h3 class="ctpl-c-types-divs-div-subheading">Reduced Schedule</h3>
                                        <p class="ctpl-c-types-divs-div-para"> A leave schedule that reduces an  employee&rsquo;s usual number of working hours per workweek, or hours per workday for a period of time, normally from a full-time schedule to a part-time schedule.
</p>
                                    </div>
                        </div>
